            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>723</offset>
                <text>At the age of our examination (16 years), the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children-Revised (WISC-R) reported a verbal IQ score of 80, a performance IQ score of 75, and a full-scale IQ score of 76, in the borderline range of intelligence.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>965</offset>
                <text>He was described by parents as being impulsive, easily distractible, with poor concentration, and oppositional behavior.</text>
                <annotation id="11">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0100710</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="37"/>
                    <text>impulsive</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="12">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000736</infon>
                    <location length="19" offset="48"/>
                    <text>easily distractible</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="13">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0031987</infon>
                    <location length="18" offset="74"/>
                    <text>poor concentration</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="14">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0010865</infon>
                    <location length="21" offset="98"/>
                    <text>oppositional behavior</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1086</offset>
                <text>This condition represents his main clinical problem as resulted in the impairment of school-related and social activities.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1209</offset>
                <text>An evaluation for ADHD was performed by a psychologist using the Diagnostic &amp; Statistical Manual for Mental Disorders [DSM-IV, 1994]: results were significant for the ADHD-combined subtype (either 6/9 inattention symptoms and 6/9 impulsivity-hyperactivity symptoms present for several years and from before the age of 7 years).</text>
                <annotation id="15">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0007018</infon>
                    <location length="4" offset="18"/>
                    <text>ADHD</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="16">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0007018</infon>
                    <location length="21" offset="167"/>
                    <text>ADHD-combined subtype</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1537</offset>
                <text>Additionally, he was presented with marked oppositional defiant disorder (ODD), as resulted from clinical observation.</text>
                <annotation id="17">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0010865</infon>
                    <location length="29" offset="43"/>
                    <text>oppositional defiant disorder</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1657</offset>
                <text>Anthropometric examination indicated short stature (159 cm, 3rd centile), low weight (48 kg, 5th centile), and normal cephalic circumference (54 cm).</text>
                <annotation id="18">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004322</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="37"/>
                    <text>short stature</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1807</offset>
                <text>Inner canthal distance was 2.7 cm (5th centile), interpupillary distance was 5 cm (5th centile), and outer canthal distance was 9.5 cm (90th centile).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1958</offset>
                <text>He had dysmorphic features including downslanting palpebral fissures with bilateral ptosis and strabismus, broad and bulbous nose, medial extension of eyebrows, dysmorphic and low set auricles, maxillary hypoplasia, ogival palatus, protuberant lips, and relative micrognathia (Fig. 1).</text>
                <annotation id="19">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000494</infon>
                    <location length="31" offset="37"/>
